DIRNAME(1)                     User Commands                     DIRNAME(1)

NAME
    dirname - strip the last component from a file name

SYNOPSIS
    dirname [OPTION] NAME...

DESCRIPTION
    Print NAME with its last non-slash component and any trailing slashes
    removed; if NAME contains no slashes, print '.' (the current directory).

        dirname /usr/share/man/tail   ->  /usr/share/man
        dirname tail                  ->  .

    This is the unmodified GNU coreutils dirname(1), ported to Horus and run
    as a ring-3 program from /bin/dirname.

OPTIONS
    -z    separate output with NUL rather than newline

    Run `dirname --help` for the full option list.

EXIT STATUS
    0 on success, non-zero on error.

SEE ALSO
    basename(1), hier(7)
